**[lint-style]** reported by [reviewdog](https://github.com/reviewdog/reviewdog) :dog:
```suggestion apply Adj.reachable h apply Adj.ne h ```

```suggestion
theorem adj_of_length_eq_one {u v : V} :  {p : G.Walk u v}, p.length = 1  G.Adj u v
```
Please add `Reachable.of_dist_ne_zero` and `exists_walk_of_dist_ne_zero`.
Good idea, working on it!
Do we want a dist_ne_zero... lemma?
This was recommended by @urkud [here](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/11945#discussion_r1569808127), I think it is a good idea because this lemma was useful in #12278.
Sorry, I meant the iff version - a normalized version of `dist_eq_zero_iff_eq_or_not_reachable.not`
Good idea, done!

```suggestion
    rw [ this.ge_iff_eq, Nat.succ_le_iff]
```

Can this use dot notation?
```suggestion
   have : h.toWalk.length = 1 := by rw [Walk.length_cons, Walk.length_nil]
```
Dot notation?

Minor golfing suggestion, otherwise LGTM. If you move `(_ : p.length = 1)` to the left of `=>`, then Lean 4 can discard the other cases automatically.
```suggestion
  | cons h nil, _ => h
```
